A bail hearing for six out of seven accused in the kidnapping and murder of a Tongaat teenager in KwaZulu-Natal continues in the Verulam Magistrate’s Court. DURBAN - Six of the seven KwaZulu-Natal men accused of killing a Tongaat teen are due back in court today for bail application. All the accused are facing charges of kidnapping and murdering Andile "Bobo" Mbuthu. READ: COVID-19 delays Tongaat court proceedings One of the accused, a 16-year-old, told the court in May that he would no longer be applying for bail. Mbuthu went missing after allegedly stealing alcohol from a local tavern. His decomposing remains were later found by police divers in a river near his home.